  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kepa and its members influence public opinion in Finland</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kepa brings together CSOs and active citizens in Finland to take part in public debate and to highlight issues of global responsibility. Kepa\&apos;s aim is to act as a platform that organisations can use in their own awareness raising and advocacy work. 

Main activities to influence public opinion are the World Village Festival, support
and networking of local organisers of the Markets of Possibilities events, supporting the
cooperation of actors of global education, Globbarit network and campaigning and ETVO Volunteer Programme. Training and communication work are included in all these activities. In addition Kepa Kepa provides
journalistic information, backgrounds and
viewpoints that other media is not offering through Kepa.fi news production, Maailman Kuvalehti magazine and social media.</narrative>
  </description>
